# ── quote-sourcing policy (copyright-safe) ──
# 1. PUBLIC-DOMAIN SOURCE ONLY. Author dead 70+ years, or an ancient/scriptural/
#    folk text. No living/recent authors, songs, films, or in-copyright works.
# 2. TRANSLATIONS ARE COPYRIGHTED. A public-domain original does NOT make an
#    English translation free — the translator holds rights. For non-English
#    sources, write a FRESH, meaning-faithful rendering in our own words and
#    mark it "(rendering)"; do not lift a specific published translation.
# 3. VERBATIM only for English-original, public-domain text (Shakespeare, the
#    KJV, Whitman, Lincoln…).
# 4. CITED and WHOLE: — Author, Work; enough to stand on its own; never a
#    paraphrase masquerading as a quote in reverse (summaries go in concepts).
